Big data refers to the collection and storage of large volumes of diverse data processed at great velocity using technological tools and analytical and advanced methods to predict consumption behaviours and patterns (data mining).; On the basis of data collected from websites, social networks, signals from smartphones or the use of payment cards, financial institutions are able to:; 

Create consumer profiles and consumption patterns;


Direct tailored financial product advertising to specific target audiences;


Assess customers’ creditworthiness.

